NT||up|34|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Before I talk about the bidding let's talk about the best way to play the hand. Because of the way the diamonds split (doubleton Q) Liza luckily made 7. But there is just about a surefire way to make 6, and likely make 7. |
PG| ***** 13 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That is to set up dummy's diamonds. So prior to drawing trump Liza should play 2 rounds of diamonds. If they split 3-2 (68%) then she can ruff a diamond high, draw trump ending in dummy with the @H10 and claim. On this hand, once the @DQ comes down, she need not even ruff the diamond, but still can draw trump and make 7 as she did. |
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The way she played it happened to make 7, but if she plays it the way I suggest it will always make 7 when diamonds are 3-2 and 6 when they are not. An alternative line is to try and ruff 3 clubs in dummy, but that is much harder than just setting up diamonds. The main point here is she should not draw trumps immediately.|
PG| ***** 15 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the bidding, it kind of depends on what you play. But Liza can just about bid 6@D with her hand, and not worry about 7. All Ruth needs is the @DA or @DQ for 6 diamonds to be a very good contract. So I probably would have bid 6@D in IMPs. |
PG| ***** 16 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In Match Points, its a little trickier, I might bid 6@H as that scores better. But Liza definitely can picture a slam so long as Ruth as the @DA or @DQ. Thus, I will argue that the weak 2 actually made it easier to get to slam. |
PG| ***** 17 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If you play in diamonds then Ruth will either be short in clubs or short in hearts. if short in clubs no problem, if short in hearts you can pitch her clubs. If you play new suits over 2@D are forcing (I do not, but most people do) the Liza can bid 2@H. If you don't play that as forcing, then you can't bid 2@H. But you should be able to picture a slam is making.|
pg| ***** 18 ***** |


